BEGIN:VCALENDAR
VERSION:2.0
PRODID:-//ridehub//RideHub//EN
X-WR-CALNAME:OBC Events (test fixture)
X-WR-TIMEZONE:America/Toronto
BEGIN:VEVENT
SUMMARY:Good Friday TT
DTSTART:20260403T150000Z
DTEND:20260403T163000Z
DTSTAMP:20260428T032428Z
UID:https://obcrides.ca/events/3345
CATEGORIES:
DESCRIPTION:<p>The annual season opener for the club's time trial events<br><br>As is our tradition\, the club's first open Time Trial (TT) of the year will be held on Good Friday (April 3).&nbsp\;<br><br>What? 15 km individual time trial. You against the clock.<br>Who? Any and all 2026 OBC members looking for a challenge.<br>Where? Meet at the parking lot of the Aviation Museum\, course is out and back along the Sir George Etienne Cartier Parkway<br>When? April 3rd\, first rider off shortly after 11 am<br>How? Pre-registration only\, closes 9 pm April 1st<br>Why? Why not? You don't need a fancy bike\, you don't need to be fast\, so come on out!</p>
LOCATION:Canada Aviation and Space Museum
URL:https://obcrides.ca/events/3345
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
SUMMARY:Sunday Ride 26-04-05 -  Nepean Sportsplex
DTSTART:20260405T140000Z
DTEND:20260405T190000Z
DTSTAMP:20260428T032428Z
UID:https://obcrides.ca/events/3117
CATEGORIES:
DESCRIPTION:<p><strong>Gentle reminder: </strong>prior to joining any OBC group rides:</p><ol data-type="decimal"><li><p>You must be a current club member\;</p></li><li><p>You must have taken the Group Riding Clinic - check this event calendar - (or be an experienced group rider who can safely ride in a peleton).</p></li></ol><h3><strong>Note for riders and leaders: road edges (e.g. Woodroffe bike lanes) will likely not have been swept\, yet. Be cautious and perhaps ride single to allow riders to more easily dodge junk on the road. Let's have no flats today!</strong></h3><h1><strong>Welcome to our returning riders and our new members!</strong></h1><h2><strong>Are you and your bike ready to go?</strong></h2><p><strong>Well\, sports fans...</strong> the weatherpeople have been steadily improving the weather outlook for the day. The latest forecast is sunny (EDIT: Not any more!) and 12 degrees\, which would be fantastic. That means I need to get off my duff\, get my bike off the trainer\, replace a chain\, swap my tires back-to-front and -- oh\, yeah -- post some routes.</p><p><strong>NOTE: </strong>recognizing that 1) the nights are still quite cool\, 2) some of of us leave home an hour in advance to ride to the starting point\, and 3) the routes are shorter in the early season\, <strong>I'm pushing back the starting time for this Sunday to 10AM.</strong></p><p>At this point\, it's safe to say that we are a GO to launch the season on April 5th <strong>BUT </strong>where the forecast for April 5th\, as of yesterday (Mar 26)\, was 12C &amp\; sunny\, it is now 12C &amp\; rainy. Good grief! A year ago\, the weather forced cancellation of the season opener\; hopefully\, that will not be repeated this year.</p><p><strong>Keep an eye on this listing for updates.</strong></p><p>If you are interested in helping out and being a ride leader this season please let Ken know at <a title="" href="mailto:kentheobcrm@gmail.com">kentheobcrm@gmail.com</a>. See the calendar for early season ride leader training and\, for new riders\, group riding clinics.</p>
LOCATION:https://maps.app.goo.gl/8gJcaGB7Fy4E6J2C7
URL:https://obcrides.ca/events/3117
END:VEVENT
