END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
SUMMARY:Sunday Ride 26-04-12 - Andrew Haydon Park
DTSTART:20260412T140000Z
DTEND:20260412T190000Z
DTSTAMP:20260428T032428Z
UID:https://obcrides.ca/events/3114
CATEGORIES:
DESCRIPTION:<p><strong>REMINDER</strong>: group ride participajnts <strong>must have previously attended </strong>an OBC Group Riding Clinic (GRC).</p><p>&nbsp\; &nbsp\; &nbsp\; &nbsp\; &nbsp\; &nbsp\; &nbsp\; &nbsp\; &nbsp\; &nbsp\; &nbsp\; &nbsp\;<a title="" href="https://ottawabicycleclub.ca/group-riding-clinics/">https://ottawabicycleclub.ca/group-riding-clinics/</a></p><h2>HELLO &amp\; WELCOME BACK!</h2><p><strong>Description:&nbsp\;</strong>Road Ride to Carp &amp\; points west</p><p><strong>Start Location:</strong> Andrew Haydon Park&nbsp\;</p><p>&nbsp\; &nbsp\; &nbsp\; &nbsp\; &nbsp\;Primary (if entry gates off of Carling Ave at Acres Rd are open): <a title="" href="https://maps.app.goo.gl/tVuuKzmsGo4UPunr7">https://maps.app.goo.gl/tVuuKzmsGo4UPunr7</a></p><p>&nbsp\; &nbsp\; &nbsp\; &nbsp\; &nbsp\;Backup (if primary gates are closed) &nbsp\;<a title="" href="https://maps.app.goo.gl/vkXWSFYihSJBxm8Y8">https://maps.app.goo.gl/vkXWSFYihSJBxm8Y8</a></p><p><strong>Start Time:</strong> 10:00 AM Departure - gather 9:30 -- 9:45</p><p><strong>New Members:</strong> If this is one of your first rides and you'd like help getting sorted out on the day\, seek me out about 20-25 minutes before departure time - ask around for "Ken" - and I'll help you get settled in.</p><p><strong>*** NOTE START TIME PUSHED TO 10:00 DUE TO COOL OVERNIGHT TEMPS FORECAST ***</strong></p><p>Sorry for the delay in getting the coming Sunday's rides posted\; I have been underwhelmed &amp\;\, indeed\, despondent by the quality of the weather that our handsomely paid forecasters are offering. Are they in contract negotiations? \;)</p><p>The forecast has\, however\, made a change for the better in the last few days\, so we'll keep our fingers crossed. Cool\, still\, but some sun in the offing.</p><p>A reminder that\, as usual\, I'm starting the season off with rides that are a little shorter.</p><p>Also\, in the early season\, pay particular attention to:</p><ul><li><p>drivers who need to relearn what bicycles are\;</p></li><li><p>remembering what road etiquette is\;</p></li><li><p>detritus on the roads and\, ESPECIALLY\, wee bits of gravel around bends on paved roads\;</p></li><li><p>other riders who are just awaking from hibernation and our new members who may be brand new to group riding\;</p></li><li><p>keeping yourself warm\, fed and watered during the rides\; and\,</p></li><li><p>when you stop -- for a flat\, a discussion\, a snack -- get off the road!</p></li></ul><p>It takes a few weeks for everyone to get back into form\; please be forgiving.</p><p><strong>COFFEE STOPS</strong></p><p>In Carp\, the new name on the old building on Donald B Munro\, just east of Carp Rd\, is Skylark Cafe. Folks may like to patronize this establishment\; I received confirmation that it will be open on Sunday. Alice's is still there but many cyclists have long memories of being banished for a few years and avoid it.</p><p>In Almonte\, there's Equator Coffee (use your RLCT swag coupon) and many other refueling establishments.</p><p></p><p>Ride leaders needed!</p><p></p><p>Bonne route!</p>
LOCATION:http://see-the-ride-description.cyc
URL:https://obcrides.ca/events/3114
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
SUMMARY:Sunday Ride 26-04-19 - Airport NRC
DTSTART:20260419T140000Z
DTEND:20260419T190000Z
DTSTAMP:20260428T032428Z
UID:https://obcrides.ca/events/3115
CATEGORIES:
DESCRIPTION:<h1>7 weeks to RLCT... Egads!</h1><hr><h2>Upcoming Club Events:</h2><p>Please take a look in the <a target="_blank" rel="noopener" title="" href="obcrides.ca">calendar</a> to see what upcoming events you may wish to take part in.</p><h3>April 23 - club social\, 5-9PM</h3><p>&nbsp\;</p><h2>Volunteer's sought and needed!!</h2><p>Your club\, and all the activities it organizes\, run on volunteers and it needs us all to pitch in\, whether a little or a lot\; every hour helps.</p><p><strong>Almonte-Paris-Roubaix </strong>If you don't mind being considered an enabler of a wild\, crazy\, often muddy\, Spring ritual\, do consider helping out with the always popular Almonte-Paris-Roubaix ride. It's sure to be rewarding! Info: <a title="" href="https://ottawabicycleclub.ca/almonte-paris-roubaix/">https://ottawabicycleclub.ca/almonte-paris-roubaix/</a></p><p><strong>Rideau Lakes Cycle Tour</strong> Whether your are planning to ride the tour or not\, there are plenty of opportunities\, either on the weekend or beforehand\, to play a small (or large!) but vital role in making it successful. <strong>Many many many volunteers are needed.</strong> Please sign up. <a title="" href="https://ottawabicycleclub.ca/rlct/">https://ottawabicycleclub.ca/rlct/</a></p><h2>This &amp\; that</h2><p>&nbsp\;<strong>Is your bike ship-shape? Are you carrying basic tools and equipment? </strong>Be sure all the critical components -- brakes\, drive train\; tires -- are in good shape and thus ensure that your bike won't be inclined to leave you in tears at the side of the road. On all club rides (in fact\, whenever you ride)\, please carry\, minimally\, a spare tube\, tire levers\, air pump (or equivalents for tubeless). Having bright\, day-time running lights (front &amp\; back) is also a really good idea to improve your visibility to drivers.&nbsp\;</p><p><strong>Keep an eye out for trash\, rocks\, sand\, gravel\, etc. on the roads\, especially rounding corners.</strong> It's unlikely that the street sweepers will be out tout de suite\, so Spring riding requires special attention to the road surface.</p><p>&nbsp\;</p><p>&nbsp\;</p><h1>On to the ride...</h1><h2>Event Description</h2><p>Road Ride from the airport to the south and southeast</p><p><strong>Start Location&nbsp\; : </strong>NRC-Airport &nbsp\;<a title="" href="https://maps.app.goo.gl/yde7tqTUGw7ka6XM8">https://maps.app.goo.gl/yde7tqTUGw7ka6XM8</a>&nbsp\;&nbsp\;</p><p><strong>Start Time&nbsp\; &nbsp\; &nbsp\; &nbsp\; &nbsp\;:</strong> <strong>10:00 AM</strong> Departure - gather 9:30-9:45</p><h2>NOTE THAT\, DUE TO THE OVERNIGHT TEMPERATURE FORECAST DROPPING SUSTANTIALLY\, THE START TIME HAS BEEN RETURNED TO 10:00AM.</h2><p>Hopefully\, you are finding mid-week days of good weather for riding\; Sundays this April are resembling last year's far too much.</p><p>This week\, we jump over to the airport for rides that will lead us to the south and southeast: Greely\, Metcalfe\, Russell\, Embrun. Some pleasant country roads.</p><p>Continue to dress for the weather.&nbsp\; According to the forecast (as of Apr 13) it may well be raining. I don't plan to cancel the ride due to rain but\, if you sign up and decide not to ride -- completely acceptable\, please cancel your registration (go to your profile on obcrides.ca) by Saturday night or early Sunday morning so others can see who still plans to ride.</p><p>Bonne route!</p>
LOCATION:https://maps.app.goo.gl/GwqoS6opaG7MonEy7
URL:https://obcrides.ca/events/3115
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
SUMMARY:OBC Spring Social + Information Session
DTSTART:20260423T210000Z
DTEND:20260424T010000Z
DTSTAMP:20260428T032428Z
UID:https://obcrides.ca/events/3180
CATEGORIES:
DESCRIPTION:<p>Join us for a relaxed evening to reconnect with riders\, meet the board\, and hear what’s planned for the 2026 season. Whether you’re a current\, former\, or brand‑new member\, this is a great chance to ask questions and get familiar with how the club works before the season kicks off.</p><p><strong>Venue:</strong> Lone Star Texas Grill1211 Lemieux Street\, Gloucester\, ON\, K1J 1A2</p><p><strong>Event Schedule</strong></p><p>5:00–7:00 PM: Social time\, meet members\, browse apparel\, visit the club table7:00–9:00 PM: Club updates + Q&amp\;A</p><p><strong>Food &amp\; Drinks</strong></p><p>Available to purchase directly from the venue.</p><p><strong>Bonus Draw</strong></p><p>If you’re already registered for 2026 or sign up on site\, you’ll be entered for a chance to win your 2026 membership fee back (conditions apply).</p><p>Please RSVP so we can plan seating and check‑in.</p><p>👉 <strong>Click below to register!</strong></p>
LOCATION:https://maps.app.goo.gl/6dhijpkEeYAxE5fV6
URL:https://obcrides.ca/events/3180
END:VEVENT
